Add ARIA live region to PackageBuilder autosave status (#2210)

Autosave outcomes ("Saved" / "Save failed") in `PackageBuilderPage` are
visual-only — screen readers are never notified. Violates WCAG 4.1.3
Status Messages (Level AA).

### Changes

- **`PackageBuilderPage.tsx`** — Wrap autosave status text in a
persistent `<Box>` live region:
  - `role="status"` / `aria-live="polite"` for success
  - `role="alert"` / `aria-live="assertive"` for failures
  - `aria-atomic="true"` so the full region is announced on change

```tsx
<Box
  role={saveStatus === "error" ? "alert" : "status"}
  aria-live={saveStatus === "error" ? "assertive" : "polite"}
  aria-atomic="true"
>
  {saveStatus === "saved" && <Typography ...>Saved</Typography>}
  {saveStatus === "error" && <Typography ...>Save failed</Typography>}
</Box>
```

- **`PackageBuilderPageAutosave.test.tsx`** — Component tests asserting
success maps to `role="status"` and failure maps to `role="alert"`

