<issue_title>[react-accessibility] Package Builder autosave status is
not announced to screen readers</issue_title>
<issue_description>## Impact
`PackageBuilderPage` shows autosave outcomes (`Saved` / `Save failed`)
only as transient visual text. Screen-reader users are not notified when
background autosave succeeds or fails, so they cannot reliably know
whether edits persisted.

WCAG: **4.1.3 Status Messages (Level AA)**.

## Reproduction Steps
1. Install deps:
   ```bash
   cd peek && npm ci --no-audit --no-fund
   ```
2. Create this new repro test at
`peek/tests/component/packageBuilderAutosaveStatus.a11y.repro.test.tsx`:
   ```tsx
   import { describe, it, expect, vi } from "vitest";
   import { render, screen, waitFor } from "`@testing-library/react`";
   import { act } from "react";

import PackageBuilderPage from
"../../src/components/PackageBuilderPage";

const { exportPackageToDirectoryMock, mockStoreState } = vi.hoisted(()
=> ({
     exportPackageToDirectoryMock: vi.fn(),
     mockStoreState: {
       currentStep: 1,
       setStep: vi.fn(),
       reset: vi.fn(),
linkedDir: { name: "fixtures-dir" } as unknown as
FileSystemDirectoryHandle,
       isLoaded: true,
       identity: { name: "demo_package" },
       policyTemplate: {},
       variables: [],
       templateContent: "",
       readmeContent: "",
     },
   }));

   vi.mock("../../src/services/packageBuilder/exportPackage", () => ({
     exportPackageToDirectory: exportPackageToDirectoryMock,
   }));

   vi.mock("../../src/store/usePackageBuilderStore", () => ({
usePackageBuilderStore: (selector: (state: typeof mockStoreState) =>
unknown) =>
       selector(mockStoreState),
   }));

vi.mock("../../src/components/packageBuilder/PackageBuilderStepper", ()
=> ({
     default: () => (div data-testid="stepper" /),
   }));

vi.mock("../../src/components/packageBuilder/PackageBuilderStartScreen",
() => ({
     default: () => (div data-testid="start-screen" /),
   }));
vi.mock("../../src/components/packageBuilder/StepIdentity", () => ({
default: () => (div)Identity(/div) }));
vi.mock("../../src/components/packageBuilder/StepSignals", () => ({
default: () => (div)Signals(/div) }));
vi.mock("../../src/components/packageBuilder/StepVariables", () => ({
default: () => (div)Variables(/div) }));
vi.mock("../../src/components/packageBuilder/StepTemplate", () => ({
default: () => (div)Template(/div) }));
vi.mock("../../src/components/packageBuilder/StepDocs", () => ({
default: () => (div)Docs(/div) }));
vi.mock("../../src/components/packageBuilder/StepExport", () => ({
default: () => (div)Export(/div) }));

   describe("PackageBuilder autosave accessibility repro", () => {
it("should expose autosave result as a status message for screen
readers", async () => {
       exportPackageToDirectoryMock.mockResolvedValue(undefined);

       render((PackageBuilderPage /));

       await act(async () => {
         await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 700));
       });

       await waitFor(() => {
         expect(screen.getByText("Saved")).toBeInTheDocument();
       });

// Repro assertion: no element with role="status" exists for the
autosave update.
       expect(screen.getByRole("status")).toHaveTextContent("Saved");
     });
   });
   ```
3. Run only the new test:
   ```bash
cd peek && npx vitest run
tests/component/packageBuilderAutosaveStatus.a11y.repro.test.tsx
--config vitest.config.ts --project dom
   ```

## Expected vs Actual
**Expected:** When autosave state changes, the update is announced
through a live region (for example `role="status"` /
`aria-live="polite"`).

**Actual:** Test fails because no status role exists:

```text
TestingLibraryElementError: Unable to find an accessible element with the role "status"
...
<span class="MuiTypography-root MuiTypography-caption ...">
  Saved
</span>
```

## Evidence
- State transitions are visual-only in
`peek/src/components/PackageBuilderPage.tsx:45-57` and `:105-115`.
- `saveStatus` is updated (`saving/saved/error`) but rendered in plain
`Typography` without live region semantics.
- I checked `/tmp/previous-findings.json`; this finding is distinct from
previously filed issues (#2156,
elastic/ai-github-actions-playground#2140,
elastic/ai-github-actions-playground#2074).

## Suggested Fix
Wrap autosave feedback in a persistent live region (e.g. `(Box
role="status" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true")...`) and use
`role="alert"` (or assertive live region) for save failures so error
announcements are not missed.

- [ ] Add live-region semantics for autosave status in
`PackageBuilderPage`
- [ ] Add a component test asserting autosave success/failure are
announced via accessibility roles




